Ivory Coast Forces Loyal to Ouattara Say They'll Advance on Capital Today

-- B y   P a u l i n e   B a x
-- 
2011-03-30T13:13:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/ivory-coast-forces-loyal-to-ouattara-say-they-ll-advance-on-capital-today.html
Troops loyal to  Alassane Ouattara ,
the internationally recognized winner of Ivory Coast’s November
election, are planning to advance on the political capital,
Yamoussoukro, today, Meite Sindou, a spokesman for Ouattara’s
prime minister, said by phone.  “We have been in touch with some of the security forces in
Yamoussoukro, we are asking them to join us,” Sindou said.
 The central market in the capital closed today after police and
security forces, which back incumbent President  Laurent Gbagbo ,
started to drive around town in large numbers, Serge Kipre, a
resident, said by phone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pauline Bax in Johannesburg at 
